The article is a message from the White House Office of the Press Secretary, discussing the continuation of the national emergency regarding the risk of nuclear proliferation caused by the accumulation of weapons-usable fissile material in Russia. The President has determined that it is necessary to extend this emergency and maintain the emergency authorities in order to respond to this threat. The United States' national security goal is to ensure that the fissile material removed from Russian nuclear weapons is used for peaceful purposes and protected from being diverted for proliferation activities.